Under the optimal conditions, the ECL response of the biosensor decreased with the increase of C(DNA), and exhibited a good linear relationship with the logarithm of C(DNA) from 100fM to 100nM (Fig. 4A and B). The linear equation was I
                        =6493–616 lgC(DNA) (fM) with a correlation coefficient of 0.9918. The detection limit of this ECL DNA biosensor was calculated to be 66fM. The linear range and detection limit of this ECL DNA biosensor was better than or at least comparable to those literatures reported before (Table 1
                        ).
